29th Road Nature Park
1502 NW 29th Road, Gainesville 32605
This park is located in the upper Hogtown Creek basin.  Bicycle paths and nature trails feature wildlife and bird watching opportunities.
Tagged as:
,
Nature
A.N.N.E. Park
6310 NW 28th Terrace, Gainesville 32653
This neighborhood park features a shady playground, picnic areas and a basketball court.
Tagged as:
,
Recreation and Play
Abby Wambach Park
4501 SW 20th Ave, Gainesville 32607
Sports lovers will want to take advantage of the many and varied playing fields in this spacious park. Dog owners will love the off-leash dog parks for their pets. Picnic tables and grills are also available for gatherings.
Tagged as:
,
Off-Leash Dog Area
,
Recreation and Play
Albert "Ray" Massey Park
1001 NW 34th St, Gainesville 32605
Albert "Ray" Massey Park is a hub of activity in NW Gainesville. It includes a beautiful park, racquetball, tennis, and basketball courts, baseball and softball fields, playground and 1.5 miles of shaded trails. The property also includes a community center and pool.
Tagged as:
,
Nature
,
Skate Parks
,
Recreation and Play
,
Community Center
,
Swimming Pool
Alfred A. Ring Nature Park
1801 NW 23rd Blvd., Gainesville 32605
Savor Nature in all of her glory as you traverse over a mile of trails winding through the forest, tracing the course of Hogtown Creek.  Amenities include a playground and a pavilion with picnic tables.
Tagged as:
,
Nature
Andrew R. Mickle, Sr. Pool
1717 SE 15th Street, Gainesville 32641
Have fun in the sun at this aquatics center!  The pool includes two diving boards, seven short-course lap lanes, pool climbing wall and more!
Tagged as:
,
Swimming Pool
Barbara Higgins Park
1352 SE 2nd St, Gainesville 32601
Barbara Higgins Park offers a pavilion, picnic tables and grills for get-togethers and there is a playground for the kids.
Tagged as:
,
Recreation and Play
Bivens Arm Nature Park
3650 S. Main Street, Gainesville 32608
Refreshed boardwalks and overlooks, new hiking trails and modern playground equipment welcome our visitors to one of Gainesville’s oldest nature parks. Scenic views abound.
Tagged as:
,
Nature
Boulware Springs Nature Park
3300 SE 15th St, Gainesville 32641
Cyclists, horseback riders and hikers, alike, will enjoy this Boulware Springs trailhead for the 17-mile Gainesville-Hawthorne State Trail.  Picnic tables, grills and restrooms are an added plus for our many visitors to Boulware Springs Nature Park.
Tagged as:
,
Nature
Broken Arrow Bluff Nature Park
5724 SW 46th Place, Gainesville 32608
Nestled between the beauty of Kanapaha Botanical Gardens and the sweeping vistas of Lake Kanapaha, Broken Arrow Bluff Nature Park provides a glimpse of Florida’s natural beauty.
Tagged as:
,
Nature
